{"Strategy":"Mainly focussing on the colors during the learning phase and already ruling out "bim" as being overall blue.
Other than that focussing on the shapes more than on the colors because some of the objects had textured parts in which they had multiple colors and there was no way for me to actually focus and memorize those colors in that short amount of time, especially since some had ~4-5 colors at the same time.
Then I watched out for the shapes the objects had, the wug looked like an eggplant on an elevated platform to me and the top was mainly a red ball on something or with things attached to it. The dep was turqoise/blue-ish with a plane platform on top of it / going into it.
That was the main strategy I used to decide to which label the objects belonged.","Issues":"at the start I didn't know how long each training-phase was (with the disappearing pictures and the labels following) so at some point I thought I had to click something to continue, but then soon after the first "break" appeared and I realized that I didn't do anything wrong.
Other than that the only thing that might've helped during the decision-tasks would've been a timer somewhere to know when the 3 seconds / 8 seconds end so that we don't panic because we don't want to run out of time.","Comment":"I liked the "calibration" with the Student-ID card because I have never seen that before"}
